SQL:
SELECT
    COUNT(cc.class_course_id)
FROM
    ClassCourse CC
JOIN Courses C ON CC.course_id = C.course_id
Join Enrollments E on E.class_course_id = cc.class_course_id
JOIN Students ST ON E.student_id = ST.student_id
JOIN Users U ON ST.student_id = U.user_id
WHERE
    U.user_id = 'HE001'  
    AND C.course_name = 'Machine Learning'

SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM Schedules s 
JOIN ClassCourse cc ON s.class_course_id = cc.class_course_id 
WHERE cc.class_id = 'IA01'

SELECT
  COUNT(DISTINCT class_id)
FROM ClassCourse
WHERE
  semester = 'FA24';

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT cc.lecturer_id) 
FROM Schedules s JOIN ClassCourse cc ON s.class_course_id = cc.class_course_id 
WHERE CAST(s.start_time AS DATE) = '2024-09-09'

SELECT MIN(start_time) 
FROM Schedules s 
JOIN ClassCourse cc ON s.class_course_id = cc.class_course_id 
JOIN Courses c ON cc.course_id = c.course_id 
WHERE c.course_name = 'Machine Learning' AND CAST(s.start_time AS DATE) = '2025-01-06'

SELECT
  COUNT(DISTINCT S.student_id)
FROM Students AS S
JOIN Majors AS M
  ON S.major_id = M.major_id
JOIN Users AS U
  ON S.student_id = U.user_id
WHERE
  M.major_name = 'Software Engineering' AND U.user_gender = 'female';

SELECT
  COUNT(*)
FROM Courses
WHERE
  course_name LIKE 'I%';

SELECT
  COUNT(DISTINCT CC.course_id)
FROM Enrollments AS E
JOIN ClassCourse AS CC
  ON E.class_course_id = CC.class_course_id
WHERE
  E.student_id = 'HE001';

SELECT
  COUNT(DISTINCT A.enrollment_id)
FROM Attendance AS A
JOIN Schedules AS S
  ON A.schedule_id = S.schedule_id
JOIN ClassCourse AS CC
  ON S.class_course_id = CC.class_course_id
JOIN Courses AS C
  ON CC.course_id = C.course_id
WHERE
  CC.class_id = 'AI01'
  AND C.course_name = 'Machine Learning'
  AND A.status = 'Present'
  AND CAST(S.start_time AS DATE) = '2025-01-08';

SELECT MAX(sgd.grade_value) 
FROM StudentGradeDetails sgd JOIN Enrollments e ON sgd.enrollment_id = e.enrollment_id 
JOIN ClassCourse cc ON e.class_course_id = cc.class_course_id 
WHERE e.student_id = 'HE001' AND cc.course_id = 'MAE'

SELECT DATENAME(weekday, s.start_time) 
FROM Schedules s 
JOIN ClassCourse cc ON s.class_course_id = cc.class_course_id 
JOIN Courses c ON cc.course_id = c.course_id 
WHERE cc.class_id = 'AI01' AND c.course_name = 'Machine Learning' 
GROUP BY DATENAME(weekday, s.start_time)

SELECT
  CC.class_id,
  C.course_name,
  U.fullname AS lecturer_name,
  S.start_time,
  S.end_time,
  S.room,
  S.slot,
  CC.semester
FROM Schedules AS S
JOIN ClassCourse AS CC
  ON S.class_course_id = CC.class_course_id
JOIN Courses AS C
  ON CC.course_id = C.course_id
JOIN Lecturers AS L
  ON CC.lecturer_id = L.lecturer_id
JOIN Users AS U
  ON L.lecturer_id = U.user_id
WHERE
  CC.semester = 'SP25';

SQL:
SELECT TOP 1 WITH TIES
    CC.class_id,
    C.course_name,
    AVG(E.average) AS AverageScore
FROM
    Enrollments AS E
JOIN
    ClassCourse AS CC ON E.class_course_id = CC.class_course_id
JOIN
    Courses AS C ON CC.course_id = C.course_id
WHERE
    E.status <> 'Studying' 
GROUP BY
    CC.class_id, C.course_name
ORDER BY
    AverageScore DESC;

SELECT C.course_name, AVG(E.average) AS AverageGrade
FROM Enrollments AS E
JOIN ClassCourse AS CC ON E.class_course_id = CC.class_course_id
JOIN Courses AS C ON CC.course_id = C.course_id
WHERE E.status <> 'Studying'

    SELECT MAX(AvgGrade)
    FROM (
        SELECT AVG(E2.average) AS AvgGrade
        FROM Enrollments AS E2
        JOIN ClassCourse AS CC2 ON E2.class_course_id = CC2.class_course_id
        JOIN Courses AS C2 ON CC2.course_id = C2.course_id
        WHERE E2.status <> 'Studying'  
        GROUP BY C2.course_name

);

SQL:
WITH RankedEnrollments AS (
  SELECT
    E.student_id,
    E.average,
    C.no_credit,
    CC.course_id,
    ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
      PARTITION BY
        E.student_id,
        CC.course_id
      ORDER BY
        TRY_CAST(RIGHT(CC.semester, 2) AS INT) DESC,
        CASE LEFT(CC.semester, 2)
          WHEN 'FA' THEN 3 
          WHEN 'SU' THEN 2 
          WHEN 'SP' THEN 1 
          ELSE 0
        END DESC,
        E.enrollment_id DESC 
    ) as rn
  FROM Enrollments AS E
  JOIN ClassCourse AS CC
    ON E.class_course_id = CC.class_course_id
  JOIN Courses AS C
    ON CC.course_id = C.course_id
  WHERE
    E.student_id = 'HE001' 
    AND E.status <> 'Studying' 
    AND C.no_credit > 0 
), FilteredEnrollments AS (
  SELECT
    student_id,
    average,
    no_credit
  FROM RankedEnrollments
  WHERE
    rn = 1 
), StudentGPA AS (
  SELECT
    FE.student_id,
    CASE 
      WHEN SUM(FE.no_credit) > 0 THEN SUM(FE.average * FE.no_credit) / CAST(SUM(FE.no_credit) AS FLOAT)
      ELSE 0
    END AS CumulativeGPA,
    SUM(FE.no_credit) as TotalCreditsConsidered
  FROM FilteredEnrollments AS FE
  GROUP BY
    FE.student_id
)
SELECT
  SG.CumulativeGPA
FROM StudentGPA AS SG

SQL:
SELECT U.fullname, E.average
FROM Enrollments AS E
JOIN Students AS S ON E.student_id = S.student_id
JOIN Users AS U ON S.student_id = U.user_id
WHERE E.average = (
    SELECT MIN(average)
    FROM Enrollments
    WHERE status <> 'Studying'
) AND E.status <> 'Studying';

SQL:
WITH RankedEnrollments AS (
  SELECT
    E.student_id,
    E.average,
    C.no_credit,
    ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
      PARTITION BY
        E.student_id,
        CC.course_id
      ORDER BY
        RIGHT(CC.semester, 2) DESC,
        CASE LEFT(CC.semester, 2)
          WHEN 'FA' THEN 3 
          WHEN 'SU' THEN 2 
          WHEN 'SP' THEN 1 
          ELSE 0
        END DESC
    ) as rn
  FROM Enrollments AS E
  JOIN ClassCourse AS CC
    ON E.class_course_id = CC.class_course_id
  JOIN Courses AS C
    ON CC.course_id = C.course_id
  WHERE
    E.status <> 'Studying' 
    AND C.no_credit > 0 
), FilteredEnrollments AS (
  SELECT
    student_id,
    average,
    no_credit
  FROM RankedEnrollments
  WHERE
    rn = 1
), StudentGPA AS (
  SELECT
    FE.student_id,
    SUM(FE.average * FE.no_credit) / SUM(FE.no_credit) AS CumulativeGPA
  FROM FilteredEnrollments AS FE
  GROUP BY
    FE.student_id
  HAVING
    SUM(FE.no_credit) > 0 
)
SELECT TOP 1 WITH TIES
  SG.student_id,
  U.fullname,
  SG.CumulativeGPA
FROM StudentGPA AS SG
JOIN Users AS U
  ON SG.student_id = U.user_id
ORDER BY
  SG.CumulativeGPA DESC;

WITH ClassScheduleCategories AS (
  SELECT
    cc.class_id,
    CASE
      WHEN CAST(s.start_time AS time) >= '07:00:00' AND CAST(s.start_time AS time) < '12:00:00'
      THEN 'Morning'
      WHEN CAST(s.start_time AS time) >= '12:00:00' AND CAST(s.start_time AS time) < '17:00:00'
      THEN 'Afternoon'
    END AS time_category
  FROM Schedules AS s
  JOIN ClassCourse AS cc
    ON s.class_course_id = cc.class_course_id
)
SELECT
  time_category,
  COUNT(DISTINCT class_id) AS class_count
FROM ClassScheduleCategories
GROUP BY
  time_category
ORDER BY
  time_category;
result: [{"time_category": "Afternoon", "class_count": 3}, {"time_category": "Morning", "class_count": 5}]
